<stack-static>
    <statement><div><p>During a Chemistry laboratory experiment at <alert>Kiharu Comprehensive School</alert>, a chemical sample contained <m>{10}^{4}</m> units of <alert>substance X</alert>.</p>

<p>By applying logarithms, write <m>{10}^{4}</m> in terms of <m>\log {10}</m>.</p>

<p><fillin characters="15" name="ans1"/>  </p></div></statement>
    <solution><div><h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>
We use the power law of logarithms:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log(a^n) = n\log a
</me>
</p>

<p>
Applying this to the expression:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\log({10}^{4}) = {4}\log {10}
</me>
</p>

<p>
So the correct answer is:
</p>

<p>
<me>
\boxed{{4}\log {10}}
</me>
</p></div></solution>
    <answer><p><m>4 \ln \left( 10 \right)</m></p></answer>
</stack-static>